'''Alan Peak''' ({{coord|72|39|S|0|11|E|}}), also known as '''Alanpiggen''', is a [[summit (topography)|peak]] at the west side of the mouth of [[Reece Valley]], in the south part of the [[Sverdrup Mountains]] in [[Queen Maud Land]]. Plotted from air photos by the [[Third German Antarctic Expedition]] (1938â39). Remapped by Norwegian cartographers from surveys and air photos by the [[Norwegian-British-Swedish Antarctic Expedition]] (NBSAE) (1949â1952) and air photos by the Norwegian expedition (1958â59). Named for [[Alan Reece]], geologist with the NBSAE (1949â52) and earlier with the [[Falkland Islands Dependencies Survey]].

